olive oil
2 clove garlic
½ head cos lettuce
1 stalk celery
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
½ tbs soy sauce
½ packet hoisin sauce
1 packet garlic aioli
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
6 Mini Flour Tortillas

• Finely chop garlic. Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients). Thinly slice celery.
Grate the carrot.

Little cooks: Kids can help wash and tear the lettuce leaves!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook pork mince, breaking it up with a spoon, until just
browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and another drizzle of olive oil to the pork and cook until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the soy sauce and hoisin sauce (see ingredients) and cook until
combined, 1 minute.

• While the pork is cooking, thinly slice fresh chilli (if using).
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until
warmed through.

Little cooks: Help warm the tortillas with oven gloves and under adult
supervision. Be careful, the plate can get hot!

• Spread a thin layer of garlic aioli over tortillas.
• Top with some cos lettuce, carrot, celery and Vietnamese-style pork.
• Garnish with chilli to serve.

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!